{
  "name": "Ninshou Theorist",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-blue.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Category: Ninjutsu</p><p>Prerequisite: Intelligence 15+, Proficiency in Ninshou</p><p>You study the Ninshou arts, gaining the following benefits:</p><p>• Increase your Intelligence score by 1, to a max of 20.</p><p>• Reduce the Downtime required to Learn, Modify, and Create Ninjutsu by 1 week, to a minimum of 1 week.</p><p>• Over the course of a short rest, you attempt to theorize and bend the chakra flow of Ninjutsu you know to be more effective.</p><p>Select a number of Ninjutsu you know equal to your Intelligence modifier (Max. 4) and make an Intelligence (Ninshou) check for each jutsu.</p><p>The DC for each check is based on the rank of the jutsu (D- Rank: 16, C-Rank: 17, B-Rank: 18, A-Rank: 19, S-Rank: 20).</p><p>On a success, until your next rest, each selected jutsu is always under one of the following Efficient Moldings from the Ninjutsu Specialist Class at no additional chakra cost (you may choose a different Efficient Molding for each jutsu).</p><p>- Careful Ninjutsu (Max of 3 creatures.)</p><p>- Distant Ninjutsu </p><p>- Piercing Ninjutsu </p><p>- Subtle Ninjutsu </p><p>- Tenacious Ninjutsu  </p><p>- Widened Ninjutsu</p>",
